node.text:
Mayweather isn't just a boxer...he's a businessman. He's built a HUGE name for himself leading to an estimated $450M net worth(other networths have been reported for 2021).

His upfront fee for his fight against Paul was said to be $10M. Overall he reported he'll make between $50M and $100M.

This is the difference between him and many athletes...it takes a great businessman to be able to make big pay days like this.

Watch the ful video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r4fcOyfVoLE&t=77s

Follow us @businessequity

node.text:
We all have the same amount of time in our days.

If you work a 9-5 it's likely that you have 2 days off a week. If you hate your current job don't slack off on the weekend. You have 48 hours (at the minimum for the entire week) to make a change.

The opportunites are endless...you can start a side hustle from basically anything. 

Follow us @businessequity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Business Equity on August 10, 2021 tagging @chitabnb. May be an image of text that says 'Chi Ta @itschitabnb How I built a $2.4M Airbnb business without owning any properties. Story time. (A thread)'.
Photo by Business Equity on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Chi Ta @itschitabnb In late 2017 my sales company went bankrupt, lost all my money and had to start all over again.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Chi Ta @itschitabnb In December 2017 didn't have enough money to pay rent and hao had to move in with my parents and I put the property was renting at the time on Airbnb.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Chi Ta @itschitabnb A month went by I noticed the property listed on Airbnb actually made more money than I was paying for rent rent at the time. At that moment I realized could turn this into a real business.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Chi Ta @itschitabnb I spent all my time learning everything could about the Airbnb business and created a strategy that allowed me to fino properties that would make me at least $2K per month after all expenses.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Chi Ta @itschitabnb I started using credit to lease properties and listed them on Airbnb with the owner's permission. By March 2018 added 7 more properties, which combined were making me $20K per month in profit.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Chi Ta @itschitabnb I ended 2018 with 30 properties and scaleo my business to $2.4M. In 2019 doubled my earnings and kept adding 1 property per month.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Chi Ta @itschitabnb During 2020 while countless people went out of business, my strategy allowed me to keep adding properties and growing my Airbnb business.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Chi Ta @itschitabnb This year my plan is to keep adding more properties and teach others how to start and grow an Airbnb business.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Chi Ta @itschitabnb This is the story of how I built my Airbnb business over the the last 3 years. If you'd like to see more content and tips about building an Airbnb business, drop me a follow.'.

Build sports car Use that money to build an affordable car Use that money to build an even more affordable car While doing above, also provide zero emission electric power generation options x BusinessEquity'.

node.text:
Most of us have pretty much watched Tesla’s master plan become reality.

Elon Musk wrote this in 2006. The first car they did was the Tesla roadster and after that came the more affordable model S and X. Then the Model 3 came out completing his goals.

To get ahead you need a vision and plan.

Follow us @businessequity
